title: Grateful Dead Live at Hofheinz Pavilion on 1977-10-14
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Mississippi Half Step-> El Paso, Brown Eyed Women, Minglewood Blues, Loser, Passenger, Friend Of The Devil, Me & My Uncle, Tennessee Jed, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Bertha-> Good Lovin', Candyman, Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around, E:Brokedown Palace-> E: Playin' In The Band

reviews.review_text:
Great show, great transfer, typical high 77' energy The real highlight is the Playin' pre-drums. Very primal with plenty of interaction between Bob and Jerry.

Thanks for this transfer.

Get it before they clump it with all the other transfers under the Road Trips release block!

Very nice show... small problem Lots of good energy. Vintage 77.

Small problem though: There's a skip in the middle of Good Lovin' -- right in the middel of "Doctor... Doc-tor!"

Good Lovin' Skip The skip has been fixed already and circulated to over 1450 downloaders on various sites.

here's the fix link:

https://www.yousendit.com/transfer.php?action=check_download&ufid=ZGJlcmxRdWNKV1B2Wmc9PQ&key=9f71fdd8313f01d2724de44473a9e7444aa11db3


Link is only good for 2 weekss.

10-14-77 With   Charlie Miller shows the sound just explodes out the speakers with great stereo sound and I swear you can hear every instrument distinctly. I love the sound of this show, and its a great performance to boot.

Comme d'habitude! Encore un excellent concert du Dead et aussi un super son!!

Merci M. Miller

Texas I really enjoyed catching this show on Sirius yesterday. I was particularly pleased when I realized that most of the songs in the first set mention either Texas or a town in Texas. Some, according to the Annotated..., mention towns that aren't in Texas but have identically named towns in the Lone Star State. A nice, fun theme that complements energetic and exploratory playing. Jerry really blows some brain cells with his phrasing throughout this show.
